data.text:
Hind Hariri Lebanese billionaire

0 0

Hind Rafik Hariri (Arabic: هند الحريري) (born in 1984) is the youngest child of Lebanese businessman and politician Rafik Hariri. She graduated from the Lebanese American University in Beirut and campaigned for her half-brother Saad in Lebanese elections. In 2008, Forbes magazine listed her as "one of the world's youngest billionaires".

Nadine Nassib Njeim Lebanese Tunisian actress and beauty queen

Nadine Nassib Njeim (NNN; Arabic: نادين نسيب نجيم‎; born 7 February 1984) is a half Lebanese and Tunisian actress and beauty pageant titleholder who was elected Miss Lebanon 2004. She represented her home country in Miss Universe 2005 in Lebanon.

Christina Sawaya Lebanese model

Christina Sawaya (Arabic: كريستينا صوايا‎) (born 16 August 1980), is a Lebanese beauty queen. As part of her modelling career, Christina entered a series of pageants between 1998 and 2002 in which she became the winner of "Miss University" Lebanon in 1998, and was chosen as "Top Lebanon Modeling 1999".
